info.senderName: NWS GreenBay (East Central Wisconsin - Green Bay)
info.headline: Flood Warning issued April 01 at 12:13PM CDT until April 02 at 7:00PM CDT by NWS GreenBay
info.description: ...The National Weather Service in Green Bay WI has issued a Flood Warning for the following rivers in Wisconsin... Yellow River at Babcock affecting Wood County. For the Yellow River...including Babcock...Minor flooding is forecast. ...FLOOD WARNING IN EFFECT FROM THIS AFTERNOON TO TOMORROW EVENING... * WHAT...Minor flooding is forecast. * WHERE...Yellow River at Babcock. * WHEN...From this afternoon to tomorrow evening. * IMPACTS...At 15.6 feet, Floodwaters are near a couple of homes in the Babcock area near Highway 173. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 11:00 AM CDT Saturday the stage was 11.9 feet. - Forecast...The river will rise above flood stage this afternoon then to 15.0 feet by tomorrow morning. It will then fall below flood stage by tomorrow afternoon. - Flood stage is 12.0 feet. - Flood History...This crest compares to a previous crest of 15.1 feet on 03/22/1953. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood &&
info.instruction: Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles. Additional information is available at www.weather.gov. The next statement will be issued late tonight.
